      "content": "It's generally recommended to wait until you finish the full course of metronidazole before consuming alcohol, as even small amounts can increase the risk of disulfiram-like effects, such as flushing and nausea, and may also reduce the medication's effectiveness. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) advise against consuming alcohol while taking metronidazole for at least 72 hours after completing the full treatment. Until then, it's best to avoid alcohol altogether.",
